coldStart.name: coldStart
coldStart.description: A coldStart trap signifies that the sending protocol entity is reinitializing itself such that the agent's configuration or the protocol entity implementation may be altered.

warmStart.name: warmStart
warmStart.description: A warmStart trap signifies that the sending protocol entity is reinitializing itself such that neither the agent configuration nor the protocol entity implementation is altered.

linkDown.name: linkDown
linkDown.description: A linkDown trap signifies that the sending protocol entity recognizes a failure in one of the communication links represented in the agent's configuration.

linkUp.name: linkUp
linkUp.description: A linkUp trap signifies that the sending protocol entity recognizes that one of the communication links represented in the agent's configuration has come up.

authenticationFailure.name: authenticationFailure
authenticationFailure.description: An authenticationFailure trap signifies that the sending protocol entity is the addressee of a protocol message that is not properly authenticated. While implementations of the SNMP must be capable of generating this trap, they must also be capable of suppressing the emission of such traps via an implementation- specific mechanism.

egpNeighborLoss.name: egpNeighborLoss
egpNeighborLoss.description: An egpNeighborLoss trap signifies that an EGP neighbor for whom the sending protocol entity was an EGP peer has been marked down and the peer relationship no longer obtains.

unspecifiedTrap.name: unspecifiedTrap
unspecifiedTrap.description: An alarm condition has occured within the unit. This trap's text will provide details on the alarm.

startDisasterRecovery.name: startDisasterRecovery
startDisasterRecovery.description: A startDisasterRecovery trap signifies that the normal external path to a remote site has been lost, and an ISDN connection to that site will be made.

stopDisasterRecovery.name: stopDisasterRecovery
stopDisasterRecovery.description: A stopDisasterRecovery trap signifies that the normal external path to a remote site has been recovered, any ISDN connections to that site will be terminated.

noBChannel.name: noBChannel
noBChannel.description: A noBChannel trap signifies that the desired call to a remote site using a phone number was unsuccessful, this phone number has now been disabled.

dailyConnLimit.name: dailyConnLimit
dailyConnLimit.description: A dailyConnLimit trap signifies that the cummulative connect time for originated calls to a remote site has been exceeded. No additional calls can be placed to this site until the next day; unless the administrator intervenes.

monthlyConnLimit.name: monthlyConnLimit
monthlyConnLimit.description: A monthlyConnLimit trap signifies that the cummulative connect time for originated calls to a remote site has been exceeded. No additional calls can be placed to this site until the next month; unless the administrator intervenes.

dataErrorBChannel.name: dataErrorBChannel
dataErrorBChannel.description: A dataErrorBChannel trap signifies that the data received on a trunk has been received in error.

pppVersion.name: pppVersion
pppVersion.description: A pppVersion trap signifies that the PPP/LCP versions used by this unit and its peer are incompatible.

ipTableFull.name: ipTableFull
ipTableFull.description: An ipTableFull trap signifies that the IP Address Table is full and another entry cannot be made at this time.

macTableFull.name: macTableFull
macTableFull.description: A macTableFull trap signifies that the MAC Address Table is full and another entry cannot be made at this time.

routeTableFull.name: routeTableFull
routeTableFull.description: A routeTableFull trap signifies that either the IP RIP, IPX RIP, or IPX SAP Table is full and another entry cannot be made at this time.

duplicateItem.name: duplicateItem
duplicateItem.description: A duplicateItem trap signifies that some protocol entity (such as an IPX Network) has been discovered at two sites.

noDChannel.name: noDChannel
noDChannel.description: A noDChannel trap signifies that the D channel connection to the switch for a port cannot be made.

lostDedicated.name: lostDedicated
lostDedicated.description: A lostDedicated trap signifies that the dedicated trunk connection has been lost.

compCallData.name: compCallData
compCallData.description: A compCallData trap signifies that the Completed Call records need to be retrieved from the unit.
